n with the breakup of the body, after death, he is reborn in the company of devas slain in battle.' What does the Blessed One have to say about that?";}i:2;i:3160;}i:85;a:3:{i:0;s:18:"doublequoteclosing";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3554;}i:86;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3555;}i:87;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3555;}i:88;a:3:{i:0;s:18:"doublequoteopening";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3557;}i:89;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:995:"Apparently, headman, I haven't been able to get past you by saying, 'Enough, headman, put that aside. Don't ask me that.' So I will simply answer you. When a warrior strives & exerts himself in battle, his mind is already seized, debased, & misdirected by the thought: 'May these beings be struck down or slaughtered or annihilated or destroyed. May they not exist.' If others then strike him down & slay him while he is thus striving & exerting himself in battle, then with the breakup of the body, after death, he is reborn in the hell called the realm of those slain in battle. But if he holds such a view as this: 'When a warrior strives & exerts himself in battle, if others then strike him down & slay him while he is striving & exerting himself in battle, then with the breakup of the body, after death, he is reborn in the company of devas slain in battle,' that is his wrong view. Now, there are two destinations for a person with wrong view, I tell you: either hell or the animal womb.";}i:2;i:3558;}i:90;a:3:{i:0;s:18:"doublequoteclosing";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4553;}i:91;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4554;}i:92;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4554;}i:93;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:93:"When this was said, Yodhajiva the headman sobbed & burst into tears. [The Blessed One said:] ";}i:2;i:4556;}i:94;a:3:{i:0;s:18:"doublequoteopening";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4649;}i:95;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:101:"That is what I couldn't get past you by saying, 'Enough, headman, put that aside. Don't ask me that.'";}i:2;i:4650;}i:96;a:3:{i:0;s:18: